---

## Conclusion

An ATX motherboard connects all major computer components such as CPU, RAM, GPU, storage, and power supply. The CPU performs processing tasks, while the chipset manages communication between different hardware parts. Understanding motherboard slots and ports is important for assembling, upgrading, and troubleshooting a computer.
